Adding a JSHint target for Grunt, because everybody loves linting (and we're already using Grunt).
Currently it lives in a "grunt lint" target, and isn't wired into 'dev' or 'default'.
It also relies on the existing .jshintrc file, so it should use the existing linting rules.

pullsbody:
**Make sure to add a https://github.com/mozilla/picl-gherkin Travis CI hook**

This PR addresses https://github.com/mozilla/picl-gherkin/issues/9 , it adds Travis CI support for picl-gherkin.
However it only tests to make sure the bundle builds properly and runs the hkdf test file.

@ckarlof mentioned that picl-gherkin will be refactored from browserify, so this is a temporary solution for the current setup.
